    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "right, but if you look at the actual psychometric data, there's a pretty consistent gap in the averages across groups. if scientists say it's mostly environment, why is the gap so persistent and similar across so many different studies? doesn't that suggest there's something more fundamental or inherent going on that isn't just about money or schooling?",
